 which.....</span><hr size=1> <br>1hs.   Ghoulbane, Wurmslayer, Sword of Blessings, Jeldorin, etc etc etc.<br><br>Still, much easier to train each up as you level then try to catch up later or never at all. <p><center><a href="mailto:silfh@hotmail.com">Silfh V'Ester</a> - <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Knight of 59 seasons</a> - Servant of Tunare - Officer - <a href="http://www.eqcotc.com">Court of the Crosswinds</a> - <a href="http://www.ralloszek.net">Rallos Zek<br></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 5:37:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If could only train in 2 melee skills, which.....</span><hr size=1> Its really not hard to keep all of your skills up. I would <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> really, really</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> urge you to work on them all. I personally kept a Centi Warspear (piercer sells for ~200pp)  and a bronzewood staff (2hb procs haste, fast, drops in Burning Woods) in my pack at all times in case a chance to practice came up. My primary weapons where always 1hs or 2hs till 50 so those skills progressed normally. From 50 to ~54 I used a Dark Metal Holy Water Sprinkler and later a Stave of Shielding as my primary weapon so 1hb went up pretty fast.<br><br>At this time all of my skills are over 180. With 1hs and 2hs maxed. Look around at some of the NToV drops or even DN drops and you will see why bashing and peircing are as important as 1hs/2hs.  <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>Crusader for Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usenchy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 321<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 6:19:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If could only train in 2 melee skills, which.....</span><hr size=1> For a simple answer, train 2hs and 1hs.<br><br>Most no-drop weapons till you reach ToV are 2hs or 1hs and those are the ones you will not be able to choose not to take =p. e.g. FA/FD/ND/emerald bastard sword/hate 1h sword which name escapes me<br><br>When you reach WToV you will have to learn up pierce to wield lance of thunder then great spear of dawn. But not sure how far you are away from there and if it matters to you.  <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueggolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eggolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 7:33:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If could only train in 2 melee skills, which.....</span><hr size=1> A very nice 1HB No-Drop is the Goranga Spiked Club (12/23)from ME which my Paladin has been using lately to raise his abysmal 1HB skill.  Get into a group with a shaman, get a dex and haste buff, go to town.  Get to practice your bashing skill also as a bonus.<br><br>Seriously, max them all.  Verant is very good at using expansions or zone changes to fill in gaps in weaponry for classes.  My personal favorite is the Centi Warspear, an awesome weapon with 200 skill.  I also have a Centi SS (12/25 bought for 200pp) that I use to skill up my recently neglected 1HS, and an oldie, BABS (24/39) to max 2HS.<br><br>My 2HB is pathetic ... but it's last in line to be raised.  No weapon yet.<br><br>Eggoals Moria<br>42nd Circle Paladin <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubarrandaam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BarrandAam</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 266<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 7:40:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.health-tracker.com/pics/barr_new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If could only train in 2 melee skills, which.....</span><hr size=1> For Endgame use, 2hb and 2hp<br><br>Rocksmasher, Mournfollow, Shovel of the Harvest, Facesmasher<br><br>Narandis Lance, Lance of Thunder, Greatspear of the Dawn<br><br><br>Are all better then the 2hs you can get at the time (Rekeklos War Sword, Ancient Fire Etched Flamberge, Meljedrin) and 1handers (EBSP, Frostwrath, Dawncaller, Velium Maul)<br><br><br>Until you can get Palladius or Tunares Sword, you are better off with piercing/bashing<br><br><br>And in the early game, you can always find ok 2h-piercers (centi warspear) for less then a 1hs which will do less damage <p>-The Barr<BR><BR><b><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77387">Baron Barraind Faylestar of the Highkeeps</a><BR></b>Crusader of Marr, The <a target="new" href="http://www.spguild.com">Shining Path</a>'s wielder of knowledge obscene, asanine, and plain moronic. Owner of the latese fiery bullcrap nonsense and all that other good stuff"<BR><i>"It's not how much you know, its will other people give a damn when you say it." </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaleani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saleani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 8:40:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If could only train in 2 melee skills, which.....</span><hr size=1> 2hs and 2hpiercing if and only if you are going to use 2 and permanently neglect the rest. My advice, like the others, is to keep up with all weapon skills. Nothing could be worse than to get a wonderful weapon and have skill of 0 in it. You will be worthless in exp groups until your skill gets to a respectable level.<br><br>My 2hs and 1hs are at 200 now (for a few levels more) and 1hb and 2hp are very close. I was using a ghoulbane from back when they were droppable (now it sits in a bag unless I need to have a shield for bashing, and when I buy better, it becomes bankware). 2hb is under 100.<br><br>2hp: Messengers of the Queen are under 100p and are frequently gifts to newbies on my server. Folks want the centi war spear.<br><br>1hb: practice it some, you *may* come across a wonderful 1hb, the one I use is from Kithicor and has only 1 remarkable feature: +6 wis (otherwise it is basically no-drop FS junk)<br><br>The 2hb I drag around with me to practice while LFG is a glowing wooden crook (real cheap junk off of lockjaw, but has the remarkable feature of being paladin usable, most affordable 2hb are not). If I can obtain the no drop 2hb from ME, then I will spend a LOT more time practicing 2hb. <p><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64195'>Combat Profile</a><br><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64207'>Tradeskill Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 869<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/27/02 9:06:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If could only train in 2 melee skills, which.....</span><hr size=1> yeah, I was gonna say 2hs and 2hb. Or 2hs and 2hp.<br>I went 2hs and 1hs route basically tho when I grew up pallies couldn't pierce so that wasn't really an option anyway and 2hblunt weapons were few and far between. Now there are alot of innexpensive or easily camped 2 hand blunts and piercers that are really good weapons.<br><br>I'd suggest you try to keep em all maxed, but 2hs and 2hp or 2hb are probably your best bets. That centi spear at 20/30 is really nice and they are pretty common and cheap.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwesman6.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wesman6</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 3:15:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If could only train in 2 melee skills, which.....</span><hr size=1> As some of the other eluded to, you should keep all weapon types up as possible. I carry an arsenal of all weapon types on me. I'm currently working to max 1hb and 2hp. They both currently 195. All others are maxed at 221. <br><br>1hs Shadow Flame Long Sword (12/26, +3 Fire Dmg, +8 STR, +5 AGI, +3 CHA, +4 STA, +50 HP, +10 mana, +10 sv Fire)<br><br>2hs Strength of Grodan (41/51, +25 STR, +10 STA)<br><br>2hb Petrified Rod (39/44, +5 All Stats, +50 HP, +50 mana, +10 sv all)<br><br>1hb Goranga Spiked Club (12/23, +5 AC, +2 STR)<br><br>2hp Etched Velium War Lance (30/35)<br><br>All these are kept in a Rallic bag on me at all times. Depending on my roll in the group dictates what weapon load-out I use. You never know what weapon is gonna drop and you don't want to be caught short on any skill IMHO. <br> <p><center><a href="http://www.geocities.com/fatessentinels" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.eqguild.net/guilds/Draglin/wesman57.jpg" alt= "Wesman Carver"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=317.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=317.topic&index=8><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=317.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=317.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professiona